<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 93 / Observer: Know thyself
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An eagle-eyed company secretary has stumbled on one reason for the alarming
weight gain in the Stock Exchange Yellow book. The new set of rules
governing listings tips the scales at 2.075kg, over twice the weight of its
predecessor.
Chapter 16, which details directors' obligations, sets out, a trifle
superfluously, how 'A company is not required to notify to the Company
Announcements Office information which, notwithstanding compliance by it
with this paragraph, it does not have.'
</TEXT>
