<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 93 / Letters to the Editor: Tecs not backing sub-standard
training
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr EDWARD ROBERTS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, The picture painted by Martin Pollard ('Incompetent trainees 'being let
loose in the workplace'', September 24) is wrong. The overwhelming majority
of Training and Enterprise Councils only fund electrical industry training
that leads to National Vocational Qualification Level 3. This is the
appropriate standard for that industry and Tecs work closely with the
industry to ensure it happens. Mr Pollard is wildly out of date.
Tecs are not in the business of funding sub-standard training. They exist to
increase the quality of training in all sectors of business and industry so
that organisations can improve their skills and competitiveness. To suggest
otherwise is thoroughly misleading.
Edward Roberts,
chairman,
TEC National Council,
24-28 Bloomsbury Way,
London WC1A 2PX
