FT  01 OCT 93 / World Trade News: US steelmakers will appeal ITC ruling
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE SIX biggest steelmakers in the US filed an appeal yesterday against an
official ruling two months ago which had overturned tarrifs aimed at
preventing dumping of foreign steel in the US.
The appeal was against rulings in 42 cases by the International Trade
Commission, mainly in the area of relatively low margin hot-rolled and
cold-rolled steel. The ITC failed to find evidence of dumping by foreign
steelmakers, leading it to overturn tarrifs imposed by the Commerce
Department.
Foreign producers have already filed their own appeals against 30 rulings
after the ITC had found evidence of dumping of the more profitable
corrosion-resistant steel. The six said they would 'vigorously defend'
against these appeals.
